From 20bb54d020522c4f509bea2bed22a3468a73ed07 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 01:03:56 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 073/174] PGCL: fix arm64/sparc arch_setup_zero_pages for
 empty_zero_page misalignment
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

After commit 5500e2631b2d ("PGCL: fix empty_zero_page alignment overflow
on alpha/microblaze") the static empty_zero_page buffer is declared with
__aligned(MMUPAGE_SIZE) when PAGE_MMUSHIFT > 0, to avoid exceeding the
assembler's maximum .align directive on alpha/microblaze.

arm64 and sparc each carry their own arch_setup_zero_pages() that
derives __zero_page directly from the empty_zero_page symbol address
(arm64 via __pa_symbol; sparc via kern_base + offset).  With the
relaxed alignment, the symbol address is no longer guaranteed to be
PAGE_SIZE aligned, so phys_to_page() returns a struct page covering
the kernel page that contains empty_zero_page _and_ adjacent BSS data.
The zero-page mapping then leaks that BSS data through reads.

This caused two LTP regressions on arm64:
  - madvise03: MAP_SIZE=8KB anon, memset(1) + MADV_DONTNEED, then read
    expects zeros — saw 0x01 (the original memset) and other BSS bytes.
  - madvise10: MAP_SIZE=16KB anon, MADV_WIPEONFORK + fork, child reads
    expect zeros — saw 0x83 at offset 3992 (random adjacent BSS).

Make arm64 and sparc allocate a fresh PAGE_SIZE-aligned zero page from
memblock when PAGE_MMUSHIFT > 0, matching the generic mm_init.c path.
The mips and s390 overrides already use memblock_alloc_or_panic, so
they were unaffected.

Verified on aarch64 QEMU: madvise03 1/0, madvise10 12/0 (both PASS).
x86_64 was unaffected because it uses the generic arch_setup_zero_pages
which already calls memblock_alloc.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/arm64/mm/init.c    | 17 +++++++++++++++++
 arch/sparc/mm/init_64.c | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 33 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/mm/init.c b/arch/arm64/mm/init.c
index 97987f850a33..1d1faafc4d8f 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/mm/init.c
+++ b/arch/arm64/mm/init.c
@@ -330,7 +330,24 @@ void __init bootmem_init(void)
 
 void __init arch_setup_zero_pages(void)
 {
+#if PAGE_MMUSHIFT > 0
+	/*
+	 * PGCL: the static empty_zero_page buffer is only MMUPAGE_SIZE
+	 * aligned (assembler limit on some arches forced relaxation in
+	 * mm_init.c).  phys_to_page() on a symbol that is not PAGE_SIZE
+	 * aligned returns a struct page covering a kernel page that also
+	 * contains adjacent BSS data, leaking it through the zero-page
+	 * mapping.  Allocate a fresh PAGE_SIZE-aligned zero page from
+	 * memblock instead.
+	 */
+	void *z = memblock_alloc(PAGE_SIZE, PAGE_SIZE);
+
+	if (!z)
+		panic("Failed to allocate zero page");
+	__zero_page = virt_to_page(z);
+#else
 	__zero_page = phys_to_page(__pa_symbol(empty_zero_page));
+#endif
 }
 
 void __init arch_mm_preinit(void)
diff --git a/arch/sparc/mm/init_64.c b/arch/sparc/mm/init_64.c
index 4f79dfa2c06f..adf9e68d9bf7 100644
--- a/arch/sparc/mm/init_64.c
+++ b/arch/sparc/mm/init_64.c
@@ -2504,10 +2504,26 @@ static void __init register_page_bootmem_info(void)
 
 void __init arch_setup_zero_pages(void)
 {
+#if PAGE_MMUSHIFT > 0
+	/*
+	 * PGCL: the static empty_zero_page buffer is only MMUPAGE_SIZE
+	 * aligned (assembler limit on some arches forced relaxation in
+	 * mm_init.c).  Using its symbol address would yield a struct
+	 * page covering a kernel page that also contains adjacent BSS
+	 * data, leaking it through the zero-page mapping.  Allocate a
+	 * fresh PAGE_SIZE-aligned zero page from memblock instead.
+	 */
+	void *z = memblock_alloc(PAGE_SIZE, PAGE_SIZE);
+
+	if (!z)
+		panic("Failed to allocate zero page");
+	__zero_page = virt_to_page(z);
+#else
 	phys_addr_t zero_page_pa = kern_base +
 		((unsigned long)&empty_zero_page[0] - KERNBASE);
 
 	__zero_page = phys_to_page(zero_page_pa);
+#endif
 }
 
 void __init mem_init(void)
-- 
